\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Consider constraints with the following format:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\sum a_{ij}\, x_{j}\{=,\leq\}b_{i}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There is a clique involving all variables in constraint 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 if:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $\underline{a}_{i}>\frac{b_{i}}{2}+\epsilon$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon$
\end_inset

 is a small constant.
 Considering that there are at most 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 coefficients in a row, C1 can be computed in linear time.
\end_layout

