\begin_layout Subsection*
Pairwise conflict detection
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the constraint do not satisfy the previously formats the algorithm
 uses a pairwise conflict detection mechanism.
 The method checks for pairs of variables in this constraint whose activation
 (or deactivation) cannot occur at the same time without violating it.
 Thus, for a constraint, pairwise conflicts detection can be computed in
 
\begin_inset Formula $O(n^{2})$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For each pair of variables, for each combination of these variable values,
 we compute a new RHS, called 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

, using the old RHS (
\begin_inset Formula $b_{i}$
\end_inset

) plus the sum of the most negative (or positive, in case of 
\begin_inset Formula $\geq$
\end_inset

 constraints) value of the other variables.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{k}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $x_{l}$
\end_inset

 the variables to be analyzed.
 The new right-hand side is calculated as follows:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $B=b_{i}-\sum_{j\in\{1..n\}\setminus\{k,\, l\}}min(0,\, aij)$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
